name: librosa
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = "0.9.2" %}
{% set hash_val = "e389bd21c2dc3922d232b13c55e9b965" %}

package:
  name: librosa
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  fn: librosa-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/l/librosa/librosa-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  md5: {{ hash_val }}

build:
  noarch: python
  number: 0
  script: {{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . --no-deps -vv

requirements:
  host:
    - pip
    - python >=3.6
    - setuptools >=48
    - wheel >=0.29.0

  run:
    - python >=3.6
    - audioread >=2.1.9
    - numpy >=1.17.0
    - scipy >=1.2.0
    - scikit-learn >=0.19.1
    - joblib >=0.14.0
    - matplotlib-base >=3.3.0
    - decorator >=4.0.10
    - resampy >=0.2.2
    - numba >=0.45.1
    - pysoundfile >=0.10.2
    - pooch >=1.0
    - packaging >=20.0

test:
  imports:
    - librosa
    - librosa.core
    - librosa.feature
    - librosa.util
    - librosa.display

about:
  home: http://github.com/librosa/librosa
  license: ISC
  summary: Python module for audio and music processing

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - bmcfee
